  "text": "In an experimental model of female Sprague-Dawley rats, which carried chemically induced (1-methyl-1-nitrosourea) mammary tumors, therapeutic XRT or tamoxifen, each given as a single modality, reduced the size of the established tumors. The combination of tamoxifen and XRT did not show the antagonistic interaction which has been demonstrated in in vitro studies. Interestingly, tamoxifen decreased the rate of radiation-induced mammary tumors in this model [CITATION_1] .",
